50|$|Regional {{political}} integration has {{not proven}} attractive to Costa Rica. The country debated {{its role in}} the <b>Central</b> <b>American</b> <b>integration</b> process under former President Calderon. Costa Rica has sought concrete economic ties with its <b>Central</b> <b>American</b> neighbors rather than the establishment of regional political institutions, and it chose not to join the <b>Central</b> <b>American</b> Parliament.|$|R
